the whole of the parisiste to consist of one chapter (the 18th) only. Roth
is also wrong in using the term Natgama Kandam as applicable to the first
three chapters of the Nirukta, the right term being Naighantuka Kandam.
Further, there are some insceuracies in the text of the Nirukta itself, which
I have pointed out in my notes. Again, there is the inexplicable inconsis-
