e. Dittography in Sanskrit Manuscripts.

On the other hand, there is also the phenomenon called dittography,
i.e. the repetition or addition of a few words or sentences. An excellent
example of dittography is furnished by The Globe on July 9, 1915.

'The Echo de Puris publishes a message from Cettinje announcing the
message from Cettinje announcing the appointment as Governor of Seutari
of Bojo Petrovitch.' * 'The part of the second line is a verbatim repetition
of a part of the first line.

In N. ii 298, ya स्य वाजी क्षिपणिं तुरण्यति स्रोवायां वद्वो अपि , . . . क्रतुं

